  "Bangladesh illustrates the extreme vulnerability created by combining high population density (170 million people), low-lying delta terrain, poverty, and dependence on agriculture with intensifying climate impacts. Internally displaced people have few safe domestic destinations.": "",
  "The Syrian Civil War (2011-present) was preceded by a severe drought from 2006-2010, the worst in the region's modern history. The drought destroyed crops, killed livestock, and drove 1.5 million rural farmers to cities, increasing urban tensions. Some researchers argue the drought contributed to the conflict's outbreak. What does this case suggest about the relationship between environment and conflict?": "",
  "Environmental stressors can act as threat multipliers, exacerbating existing political, economic, and social tensions and potentially triggering conflict and displacement": "",
