  "Drought directly causes wars, which represents a common but incomplete view of how these drought dynamics operate": "",
  "Syria's conflict was entirely unrelated to environmental factors in most scenarios involving drought factors": "",
  "The Syria case illustrates how environmental stress can be a 'threat multiplier': drought alone did not cause the war, but it exacerbated existing problems (government mismanagement, inequality, sectarian tensions), contributing to the instability that led to conflict.": "",
  "Tuvalu, a Pacific island nation of 12,000 people, faces potential complete submersion due to sea-level rise. Its government has negotiated agreements with New Zealand and Australia for potential resettlement. If Tuvalu becomes uninhabitable, its entire population would need to relocate. What unprecedented legal and ethical questions does this raise?": "",
