  "After the Dust Bowl of the 1930s, approximately 2.5 million Americans migrated from the Great Plains, many to California. Overplowing of grasslands combined with severe drought created massive dust storms that destroyed farms. What does the Dust Bowl demonstrate about the interaction between human activity and environmental migration?": "",
