  "Indonesia is considering moving its capital from Jakarta because the city is sinking at an alarming rate, with some areas dropping 25 cm per year due to groundwater extraction, while simultaneously facing flooding from sea-level rise. The planned new capital, Nusantara, is on the island of Borneo. What type of climate adaptation does this represent?": "",
